About 19 Gupta-linked companies had approached the court wanting to compel the Bank of Baroda to continue offering services to them. Bank of Baroda was the last bank to offer services to Gupta family businesses after all major South African banks closed their accounts over suspected illicit financial flows. Earlier this year the Indian-based bank announced that it would be shutting down its operation in South Africa. Advocate Tiro Moretlwe, representing the Gupta companies, says his instruction was to accept the verdict and refused to comment further.

--Additional copy by ANA--

